<h1>Problem 1250 - 2005 IMOSL, N6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(a\), \(b\) be positive integers such that \(b^n+n\) is a multiple of \(a^n+n\) for all positive integers \(n\). Prove that \(a=b\).</p>
